## (3)(a) Cloud Deployment Models

> Describe the deployment models of Cloud Computing based on location and distribution. *(5 marks)*

---

| Model | Description | Use Case |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| **Public Cloud** | Resources shared among multiple organizations, owned by provider | Startups, web apps |
| **Private Cloud** | Dedicated to single organization, on-premises or hosted | Banks, healthcare |
| **Hybrid Cloud** | Combination of public and private | Burst capacity, sensitive data |
| **Community Cloud** | Shared by organizations with common concerns | Government, research |

---

**Public Cloud:**
- Lowest cost, pay-per-use
- Managed by third party (AWS, Azure, Google)
- Less control, shared resources

**Private Cloud:**
- Maximum control and security
- Higher cost (own infrastructure)
- Dedicated resources

**Hybrid Cloud:**
- Best of both worlds
- Keep sensitive data private, burst to public for peaks

