## (3)(b) Cloud Delivery Models

> Provide the cloud delivery models and describe for each model one example using Amazon, Google or Microsoft products. *(5 marks)*

---

| Model | What You Get | Example |
|-------|--------------|---------|
| **IaaS** | Virtual machines, storage, networks | **AWS EC2** |
| **PaaS** | Platform to build/deploy apps | **Google App Engine** |
| **SaaS** | Ready-to-use applications | **Microsoft 365** |

---

**IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service):**
- **AWS EC2** - rent virtual servers by the hour
- You manage: OS, middleware, applications
- Provider manages: hardware, virtualization, networking

**PaaS (Platform as a Service):**
- **Google App Engine** - deploy code, platform handles scaling
- You manage: application code
- Provider manages: runtime, OS, servers

**SaaS (Software as a Service):**
- **Microsoft 365** - use Word, Excel, Teams in browser
- You manage: your data
- Provider manages: everything else

