## (3)(c) Performance Metrics

> Give and compare at least three user-perceived and three provider-centric performance metrics. *(5 marks)*

---

**User-Perceived Metrics:**

| Metric | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Response Time** | Time from request to response |
| **Availability** | Uptime percentage (e.g., 99.9%) |
| **Throughput** | Requests handled per second |

---

**Provider-Centric Metrics:**

| Metric | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Resource Utilization** | CPU, memory, storage usage |
| **Energy Efficiency** | Power consumption per workload |
| **Cost per Transaction** | Operational cost to serve requests |

---

**Comparison:**

| Aspect | User-Perceived | Provider-Centric |
|--------|----------------|------------------|
| **Focus** | Experience quality | Operational efficiency |
| **Goal** | Minimize latency, maximize uptime | Minimize cost, maximize utilization |
| **Conflict** | Users want dedicated resources | Providers want to share resources |

> **Trade-off:** High resource utilization (good for provider) can hurt response time (bad for user).

